{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "skinsolidify", "icon": "SOP/skinsolidify", "tags": "character, rigging, skin, vellum", "since": "19.0", "version": "", "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Skin Solidify"], "extent": [128, 146]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Converts surface geometry to a solid (tetrahedrons) and prepares the output geometry for solving with a skin solver."], "extent": [146, 271]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node constructs the Skin pass (Skin Surface Layer and Skin Solid Layer) from an input polygonal surface."], "extent": [271, 382]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 0, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/musclestissue_skinsolidifylayers.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [382, 451], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "left full"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "note", "indent": 0, "text": ["Important Note"], "role": "item", "extent": [480, 502], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Applying a Skin pass to your character is ", {"type": "em", "text": ["optional"]}, ". You can achieve many Muscle & Tissue simulation looks with ", {"type": "em", "text": ["only"]}, " the Tissue pass. Adding Skin Layers to your character lets you to create finer wrinkling and folding skin effects."], "extent": [502, 742]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The first input (Input 1) on this node provides the surface geometry from which to generate the Skin pass\u2019s outer polygonal surface (Skin Surface Layer) and its inner tetrahedra (Skin Solid Layer). The surface geometry must be triangulated ", {"type": "em", "text": ["before"]}, " tetrahedralization. If the surface isn\u2019t already made of triangles, you can use the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Remesh Exterior Surface"]}, " parameters on this node to triangulate it. For more control over how the surface geometry\u2019s polygons are triangulated, you can use an external ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/remesh.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/remesh.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/remesh", "type": "link", "text": ["Remesh SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/remesh.html"}, " node instead."], "extent": [742, 1319]}, {"type": "col_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1319, 1326], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["In most cases, this node\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Skin Thickness"]}, " parameter value should match the value of the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Inset"]}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/tissuesolidify.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/tissuesolidify.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify", "type": "link", "text": ["Tissue Solidify SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify.html"}, " node upstream. However, this is not a requirement. The innermost boundary of the Skin Solid Layer is constrained to the Tissue Surface Layer. You can affect how strong and how tight the attach constraint is by modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Layer \u25b8 Attach"]}, "-type parameters on the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/skinproperties.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/skinproperties.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/skinproperties", "type": "link", "text": ["Skin Properties SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skinproperties.html"}, " node."], "extent": [1326, 1904]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1904, 1915], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can use an ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/attribpaint.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/attribpaint.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribpaint", "type": "link", "text": ["Attrib Paint SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribpaint.html"}, " node to paint a thickness multiplier attribute to customize and vary the skin\u2019s thickness. You can use the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Thickness Multiplier Attribute"]}, " parameter on this node to specify the name of that painted attribute."], "extent": [1915, 2225]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [2225, 2232], "body": [{"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/musclestissue_skinesolidifycrosssection.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [2232, 2312], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 8, "text": ["Cross section showing the Skin Layers"], "extent": [2340, 2393]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "left wide"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2497, 2509], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Skin Thickness"], "extent": [2509, 2526], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Specifies how deep the Skin Solid Layer (tetrahedral mesh) should be and determines the distance from the Skin Surface Layer to the Tissue Surface Layer. This parameter is also closely related to the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify#surfaceoffset", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface Offset"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify.html#surfaceoffset", "fragment": "#surfaceoffset"}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/tissuesolidify.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/tissuesolidify.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify", "type": "link", "text": ["Tissue Solidify SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify.html"}, " node."], "extent": [2550, 2916]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "tip", "indent": 4, "text": ["Tips"], "role": "item", "extent": [2916, 2931], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["If you want the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Skin Thickness"]}, " parameter\u2019s value to be the same as the value of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify#surfaceoffset", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface Offset"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify.html#surfaceoffset", "fragment": "#surfaceoffset"}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/tissuesolidify.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/tissuesolidify.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify", "type": "link", "text": ["Tissue Solidfy SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify.html"}, " node, then you can create a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["channel reference"]}, " by copying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Offset"]}, " value and pasting it to the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Skin Thickness"]}, " field as a relative reference ( ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"keys": ["RMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " \u25b8 Paste Relative Reference"]}, ")."], "extent": [2931, 3385]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["when ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Offset"]}, " is larger than the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Skin Thickness"]}, ", you can achieve more surface detail and muscle definition as this will cause the the skin to seek out all the crevices."], "extent": [3385, 3579]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "skinthickness"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Thickness Multiplier Attribute"], "extent": [3579, 3611], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When on, specifies the name of the attribute (", {"type": "code", "text": ["skinthickness"]}, " by default) you can use to vary the thickness of the skin\u2019s tetrahedra. The value of this attribute is a multiplier for the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Skin Thickness"]}, " parameter. You can use an ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/attribpaint.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/attribpaint.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribpaint", "type": "link", "text": ["Attrib Paint SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribpaint.html"}, " node to paint this attribute on your character\u2019s skin to vary its thickness in the painted areas."], "extent": [3637, 4045]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "thicknessattrib"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Regular Layers"], "extent": [4045, 4061], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determines how many layers of tetrahedrons are packed into the overall skin thickness."], "extent": [4081, 4173]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "numlayers"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Blurring Iterations"], "extent": [4173, 4194], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Averaging point positions on the interior surface ot the skin layer can help smooth out imperfections and anomalies.  This parameter determines the number of smoothing iterations to apply."], "extent": [4223, 4417]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "blurringiterations"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Step Size"], "extent": [4417, 4428], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Size of each iteration when blurring."], "extent": [4447, 4490]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "stepsize"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "type": "sep", "indent": 0, "text": [" Remesh Surfaces "], "extent": [4490, 4514], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["See the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "/icons/SOP/remesh.svg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/icons/SOP/remesh.svg.html"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/remesh", "type": "link", "text": ["Remesh SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/remesh.html"}, " node\u2019s documentation."], "extent": [4538, 4632]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "remeshsurface"}}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [4632, 4640], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Input 1"], "extent": [4640, 4650], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The surface polygons from which to generate the Skin pass (Skin Surface Layer and Skin Solid Layer)."], "extent": [4650, 4756]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [4756, 4765], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Output 1"], "extent": [4765, 4776], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Skin pass, which includes the Skin Surface Layer (polygons) and the Skin Solid Layer (tetrahedra)."], "extent": [4776, 4884]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Outputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [4884, 4893], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/skinproperties", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skinproperties.html"}], "extent": [4893, 4921]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tissuesolidify.html"}], "extent": [4921, 4950]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Skin Solidify"], "summary": ["Converts surface geometry to a solid (tetrahedrons) and prepares the output geometry for solving with a skin solver."]}